{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1015,"text":"If you've been thinking about US politics"},{"time":4320,"text":"and trying to make sense of it\nfor the last year or so,"},{"time":8807,"text":"you might have hit on something\nlike the following three propositions:"},{"time":13046,"text":"one, US partisanship\nhas never been so bad before;"},{"time":19212,"text":"two,"},{"time":20792,"text":"for the first time,\nit's geographically spatialized --"},{"time":24590,"text":"we're divided between the coasts,\nwhich want to look outwards,"},{"time":28561,"text":"and the center of the country,\nwhich wants to look inwards;"},{"time":31702,"text":"and third,"},{"time":33005,"text":"there's nothing we can do about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37230,"text":"I'm here to today to say\nthat all three of these propositions,"},{"time":40935,"text":"all of which sound reasonable,"},{"time":42963,"text":"are not true."},{"time":45075,"text":"In fact,"},{"time":46300,"text":"our US partisanship goes all the way back"},{"time":49645,"text":"to the very beginning of the republic."},{"time":53427,"text":"It was geographically spatialized\nin almost eerily the same way"},{"time":58534,"text":"that it is today,"},{"time":59851,"text":"and it often has been\nthroughout US history."},{"time":63822,"text":"And last,"},{"time":64996,"text":"and by far most importantly,"},{"time":67394,"text":"we actually have\nan extraordinary mechanism"},{"time":71720,"text":"that's designed to help us manage\nfactional disagreement and partisanship."},{"time":77613,"text":"That technology is the Constitution."},{"time":81261,"text":"And this is an evolving, subtly,\nsupplely designed entity"},{"time":87179,"text":"that has the specific purpose"},{"time":88743,"text":"of teaching us how to manage\nfactional disagreement"},{"time":92252,"text":"where it's possible to do that,"},{"time":94170,"text":"and giving us techniques\nfor overcoming that disagreement"},{"time":97875,"text":"when that's possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99951,"text":"Now, in order to tell you the story,"},{"time":102486,"text":"I want to go back\nto a pivotal moment in US history,"},{"time":106774,"text":"and that is the moment"},{"time":107953,"text":"when factional disagreement\nand partisanship was born."},{"time":111977,"text":"There actually was a birth moment --"},{"time":113820,"text":"a moment in US history\nwhen partisanship snapped into place."},{"time":118781,"text":"The person who's at the core\nof that story is James Madison."},{"time":124192,"text":"And at the moment that this began,"},{"time":126945,"text":"James Madison was riding high."},{"time":130180,"text":"He himself was the Einstein\nof not only the US Constitution,"},{"time":134675,"text":"but of constitutional thought\nmore globally,"},{"time":137164,"text":"and, to give him his due,"},{"time":139217,"text":"he knew it."},{"time":141325,"text":"In a period of time of just three years,"},{"time":144443,"text":"from 1785 to 1788,"},{"time":146825,"text":"he had conceived, theorized,\ndesigned, passed and gotten ratified"},{"time":153248,"text":"the US Constitution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154813,"text":"And just to give you\nsome sense of the enormity"},{"time":157074,"text":"of what that accomplishment actually was,"},{"time":159170,"text":"although Madison\ncouldn't have known it at the time,"},{"time":162089,"text":"today that same constitutional technology\nthat he invented is still in use"},{"time":167424,"text":"not only in the US,"},{"time":169129,"text":"but, 230 years later,"},{"time":170637,"text":"in places like Canada,"},{"time":173004,"text":"India,"},{"time":174848,"text":"South Africa,"},{"time":176395,"text":"Brazil."},{"time":178017,"text":"So in an extraordinary range\nof contexts all over the world,"},{"time":180921,"text":"this technology is still the dominant,"},{"time":183025,"text":"most used, most effective technology\nto manage governance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187996,"text":"In that moment,"},{"time":189961,"text":"Madison believed that,\nhaving solved this problem,"},{"time":193557,"text":"the country would run smoothly,"},{"time":195196,"text":"and that he had designed a technology"},{"time":197028,"text":"that would minimize\nthe results of factions"},{"time":200098,"text":"so there would be no political parties."},{"time":202294,"text":"Remarkably, he thought\nhe had designed a constitution"},{"time":204827,"text":"that was against political parties"},{"time":206550,"text":"and would make them unnecessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208500,"text":"He had gotten an enormous degree of help"},{"time":210430,"text":"in the final marketing phase\nof his constitutional project"},{"time":214297,"text":"from a man you may have heard of,\ncalled Alexander Hamilton."},{"time":218493,"text":"Now, Hamilton was everything\nMadison was not."},{"time":222314,"text":"He was passionate,\nwhere Madison was restrained."},{"time":226729,"text":"He was pansexual,"},{"time":228601,"text":"where Madison didn't speak\nto a woman expect for once"},{"time":231465,"text":"until he was 42 years old,"},{"time":233079,"text":"and then married Dolley\nand lived happily ever after for 40 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236756,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238383,"text":"To put it bluntly,"},{"time":239567,"text":"Hamilton's the kind of person"},{"time":240998,"text":"about whom you would write\na hip-hop musical --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243251,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244302,"text":"and Madison is the kind of person"},{"time":245914,"text":"about whom you would not write\na hip-hop musical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248343,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249387,"text":"Or indeed, a musical of any kind at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252372,"text":"But together,"},{"time":253565,"text":"they had become a rather unlikely pairing,"},{"time":255661,"text":"and they had produced\nthe Federalist Papers,"},{"time":257734,"text":"which offered a justification"},{"time":259830,"text":"and, as I mentioned,"},{"time":261019,"text":"a marketing plan for the Constitution,"},{"time":263279,"text":"which had been wildly effective\nand wildly successful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268529,"text":"Once the new government was in place,"},{"time":270323,"text":"Hamilton became Secretary of the Treasury,"},{"time":272494,"text":"and he had a very specific idea in mind."},{"time":275208,"text":"And that was"},{"time":276385,"text":"to do for financial institutions\nand infrastructure"},{"time":279380,"text":"exactly what Madison had done\nfor constitutions."},{"time":283665,"text":"Again, his contemporaries all knew it."},{"time":285868,"text":"One of them told Madison,"},{"time":287726,"text":"who can't have liked it very much,"},{"time":289503,"text":"that Hamilton was the Newton\nof infrastructure."},{"time":293394,"text":"The idea was pretty straightforward."},{"time":295575,"text":"Hamilton would give\nthe United States a national bank,"},{"time":298970,"text":"a permanent national debt --"},{"time":302400,"text":"he said it would be\n\"immortal,\" his phrase --"},{"time":305667,"text":"and a manufacturing policy\nthat would enable trade and manufacturing"},{"time":311270,"text":"rather than agriculture,"},{"time":312852,"text":"which was where the country's primary\nwealth had historically been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317458,"text":"Madison went utterly ballistic."},{"time":320604,"text":"And in this pivotal, critical decision,"},{"time":323659,"text":"instead of just telling the world\nthat his old friend Hamilton was wrong"},{"time":327930,"text":"and was adopting the wrong policies,"},{"time":330653,"text":"he actually began to argue"},{"time":332439,"text":"that Hamilton's ideas\nwere unconstitutional --"},{"time":335564,"text":"that they violated the very nature\nof the Constitution"},{"time":338558,"text":"that the two of them had drafted together."},{"time":342317,"text":"Hamilton responded\nthe way you would expect."},{"time":346194,"text":"He declared Madison to be\nhis \"personal and political enemy\" --"},{"time":351279,"text":"these are his words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352848,"text":"So these two founders who had been\nsuch close friends and such close allies"},{"time":356831,"text":"and such partners,"},{"time":358097,"text":"then began to produce enmity."},{"time":361782,"text":"And they did it in the good,\nold-fashioned way."},{"time":364054,"text":"First, they founded political parties."},{"time":365924,"text":"Madison created a party originally called\nthe Democratic Republican Party --"},{"time":369532,"text":"\"Republican\" for short --"},{"time":370766,"text":"and Hamilton created a party\ncalled the Federalist Party."},{"time":374493,"text":"Those two parties adopted\npositions on national politics"},{"time":378164,"text":"that were extreme and exaggerated."},{"time":380905,"text":"To give you a clear example:"},{"time":382663,"text":"Madison, who had always believed"},{"time":384235,"text":"that the country would have\nsome manufacturing and some trade"},{"time":387348,"text":"and some agriculture,"},{"time":388942,"text":"began attacking Hamilton"},{"time":391174,"text":"as a kind of tool of the financial markets"},{"time":395372,"text":"whom Hamilton himself intended\nto put in charge of the country."},{"time":400710,"text":"That was an overstatement,"},{"time":402024,"text":"but it was something\nMadison came to believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404168,"text":"He also attacked city life,"},{"time":406061,"text":"and he said that the coasts were corrupt,"},{"time":408890,"text":"and what people needed to do\nwas to look inwards"},{"time":411545,"text":"to the center of the country,"},{"time":413282,"text":"to farmers, who were the essence\nof Republican virtue,"},{"time":417119,"text":"and they should go back to the values\nthat had made American great,"},{"time":420995,"text":"specifically the values of the Revolution,"},{"time":423837,"text":"and those were the values of low taxes,"},{"time":426362,"text":"agriculture"},{"time":427547,"text":"and less trade."},{"time":429411,"text":"Hamilton responded to this\nby saying that Madison was naïve,"},{"time":434112,"text":"that he was childish,"},{"time":436280,"text":"and that his goal was\nto turn the United States"},{"time":438745,"text":"into a primitive autarchy,"},{"time":440564,"text":"self-reliant and completely ineffectual\non the global scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444423,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":445958,"text":"They both meant it,"},{"time":447687,"text":"and there was some truth\nto each of their claims,"},{"time":450066,"text":"because each side was grossly exaggerating\nthe views of the other"},{"time":454432,"text":"in order to fight their war."},{"time":456902,"text":"They founded newspapers,"},{"time":459059,"text":"and so for the first time in US history,"},{"time":461028,"text":"the news that people received\ncame entirely through the lens"},{"time":466012,"text":"of either the Republican\nor the Federalist party."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471059,"text":"How does this end?"},{"time":473251,"text":"Well, as it turned out,\nthe Constitution did its work."},{"time":477939,"text":"But it did its work in surprising ways"},{"time":481023,"text":"that Madison himself\nhad not fully anticipated."},{"time":486827,"text":"First, there was a series of elections."},{"time":489238,"text":"And the first two times out of the box,"},{"time":491853,"text":"the Federalists destroyed the Republicans."},{"time":496860,"text":"Madison was astonished."},{"time":499978,"text":"Of course, he blamed the press."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501682,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504044,"text":"And in a rather innovative view --"},{"time":506367,"text":"Madison never failed to innovate\nwhen he thought about anything --"},{"time":509577,"text":"he said the reason\nthat the press was so pro-Federalist"},{"time":512266,"text":"is that the advertisers\nwere all Federalists,"},{"time":515665,"text":"because they were traders on the coasts\nwho got their capital from Britain,"},{"time":520416,"text":"which Federalism was in bed with."},{"time":523796,"text":"That was his initial explanation."},{"time":526232,"text":"But despite the fact that the Federalists,"},{"time":528304,"text":"once in power,"},{"time":529479,"text":"actually enacted laws that criminalized\ncriticism of the government --"},{"time":534728,"text":"that happened in the United States --"},{"time":537746,"text":"nevertheless,"},{"time":539535,"text":"the Republicans fought back,"},{"time":541246,"text":"and Madison began to emphasize\nthe freedom of speech,"},{"time":544573,"text":"which he had built\ninto the Bill of Rights,"},{"time":547085,"text":"and the capacity of civil society"},{"time":549244,"text":"to organize."},{"time":550634,"text":"And sure enough, nationally,"},{"time":553280,"text":"small local groups -- they were called\nDemocratic-Republican Societies --"},{"time":557667,"text":"began to form and protest\nagainst Federalist-dominated hegemony."},{"time":563136,"text":"Eventually, the Republicans managed\nto win a national election --"},{"time":568397,"text":"that was in 1800."},{"time":570585,"text":"Madison became the Secretary of State,"},{"time":572829,"text":"his friend and mentor Jefferson\nbecame president,"},{"time":575543,"text":"and they actually, over time,"},{"time":577789,"text":"managed to put the Federalists\ncompletely out of business."},{"time":582665,"text":"That was their goal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585826,"text":"Now, why did that happen?"},{"time":588668,"text":"It happened because in the structure\nof the Constitution"},{"time":592513,"text":"were several features\nthat actually managed faction"},{"time":596297,"text":"the way there were supposed to do\nin the first place."},{"time":598851,"text":"What were those?"},{"time":600515,"text":"One -- most important of all --"},{"time":602815,"text":"the freedom of speech."},{"time":604653,"text":"This was an innovative idea at the time."},{"time":606834,"text":"Namely, that if you were out of power,"},{"time":609117,"text":"you could still say\nthat the government was terrible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612960,"text":"Two,"},{"time":614890,"text":"civil society organization."},{"time":617051,"text":"The capacity to put together\nprivate groups, individuals,"},{"time":621189,"text":"political parties and others"},{"time":622820,"text":"who would organize to try to bring\nabout fundamental change."},{"time":627933,"text":"Perhaps most significantly\nwas the separation of powers --"},{"time":632154,"text":"an extraordinary component\nof the Constitution."},{"time":635139,"text":"The thing about the separation of powers"},{"time":637111,"text":"is that it did then and it does now,"},{"time":639609,"text":"drive governance to the center."},{"time":644126,"text":"You can get elected to office\nin the United States"},{"time":647462,"text":"with help from the periphery,"},{"time":649454,"text":"right or left."},{"time":651476,"text":"It turns out,"},{"time":652760,"text":"you actually can't govern\nunless you bring on board the center."},{"time":658980,"text":"There are midterm elections\nthat come incredibly fast"},{"time":662722,"text":"after a presidency begins."},{"time":665777,"text":"Those drive presidents towards the center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669168,"text":"There's a structure in which\nthe president, in fact, does not rule"},{"time":673497,"text":"or even govern,"},{"time":674932,"text":"but can only propose laws\nwhich other people have to agree with --"},{"time":679572,"text":"another feature that tends\nto drive presidents"},{"time":682178,"text":"who actually want to get things done"},{"time":683960,"text":"to the center."},{"time":685553,"text":"And a glance at the newspapers today\nwill reveal to you"},{"time":689809,"text":"that these principles are still\ncompletely in operation."},{"time":694351,"text":"No matter how a president gets elected,"},{"time":696505,"text":"the president cannot get anything done"},{"time":700005,"text":"unless the president first of all\nfollows the rules of the Constitution,"},{"time":703715,"text":"because if not,"},{"time":704895,"text":"the courts will stand up,\nas indeed has sometimes occurred,"},{"time":708216,"text":"not only recently,\nbut in the past, in US history."},{"time":711100,"text":"And furthermore,"},{"time":712277,"text":"the president needs people,"},{"time":713871,"text":"elected officials who know\nthey need to win election"},{"time":716967,"text":"from centrist voters,"},{"time":718436,"text":"also to back his or her policies\nin order to pass laws."},{"time":723562,"text":"Without it, nothing much happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727865,"text":"The takeaway of this brief excursus"},{"time":731461,"text":"into the history of partisanship,\nthen, is the following:"},{"time":737498,"text":"partisanship is real;"},{"time":740048,"text":"it's profound;"},{"time":742009,"text":"it's extraordinarily powerful,"},{"time":744465,"text":"and it's terribly upsetting."},{"time":747495,"text":"But the design of the Constitution\nis greater than partisanship."},{"time":754278,"text":"It enables us to manage partisanship\nwhen that's possible,"},{"time":758735,"text":"and it enables us actually\nto overcome partisan division"},{"time":764735,"text":"and produce compromise,"},{"time":766407,"text":"when and only when that is possible."},{"time":771083,"text":"A technology like that\nis a technology that worked"},{"time":774609,"text":"for the founders,"},{"time":776350,"text":"it worked for their grandchildren,"},{"time":780084,"text":"it didn't work at the moment\nof the Civil War,"},{"time":782316,"text":"but then it started working again."},{"time":784665,"text":"And it worked for our grandparents,"},{"time":786990,"text":"our parents,"},{"time":788568,"text":"and it's going to work for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793468,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798725,"text":"So what you should do is really simple."},{"time":801769,"text":"Stand up for what you believe in,"},{"time":804387,"text":"support the organizations\nthat you care about,"},{"time":807617,"text":"speak out on the issues\nthat matter to you,"},{"time":811425,"text":"get involved,"},{"time":813280,"text":"make change,"},{"time":814819,"text":"express you opinion,"},{"time":816738,"text":"and do it with respect\nand knowledge and confidence"},{"time":820613,"text":"that it's only by working together"},{"time":823491,"text":"that the constitutional technology\ncan do the job that it is designed to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828997,"text":"Stand up for what you believe,"},{"time":830714,"text":"but take a deep breath while you do it."},{"time":833358,"text":"It's going to be OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837067,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838450,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}